    Authoring rules honored (per AAP Sections 0.7.1 / 0.7.2 and the
    agent prompt's eight authoring rules):

      Rule 1 - Synthetic only (AAP Section 0.7.2 NO-PII clause):
        subject = "Demo task 04: Final review for resolution"
                  (synthetic identifier using the literal word "Demo"
                   plus a numeral plus a generic case-handling-action
                   phrase "Final review for resolution"; "Final review"
                   is a generic activity descriptor, NOT a real
                   person's name or specific incident; "for resolution"
                   is a generic preposition phrase indicating purpose,
                   not a real organization or location; no PII; the
                   wording emphasizes the task's lifecycle role - the
                   agent's final pre-resolution sign-off check that
                   matches the Review task type semantically)
        NO description / NO details / NO comments fields populated;
        the task's primary content is captured in the subject alone.
        NO assignee email, phone, or other PII-bearing fields.

      Rule 2 - Choice value precision (CRITICAL FOR THIS TASK):
        type   = "Review"  (exactly as registered in
                  ../../choices/sys_choice_case_task_type.xml; the
                  second value of the four task types - Investigation,
                  Review, Follow-up, Other; capital R deliberate -
                  "Review" not "review" or "REVIEW" or any other
                  casing/pluralization. THIS VALUE IS LOAD-BEARING
                  because this task is one of two demonstrators of the
                  `Review` choice value (the other being task 08 on
                  case 09); without this task's exact match, the
                  General Inquiry flow's resolve-success pair would
                  lack a Review-typed exercise. The Review type
