                  validation activity - reading through the case one
                  final time, confirming the body and assignments are
                  correct, and signing off before manager-approved
                  resolution. Verifiable with: grep -E
                  '<type>Review</type>' returns exactly 1 match in
                  this file.)
        status = "Closed"  (exactly as registered in
                  ../../choices/sys_choice_case_task_status.xml; the
                  third and terminal value of the three task statuses
                  - Open, In Progress, Closed; capital C deliberate -
                  "Closed" NOT "closed" (lowercase), NOT "CLOSED" (all
                  uppercase), NOT "Close" (verb form), NOT "Done" or
                  "Complete" (alternative terms not in the choice
                  list). THIS VALUE IS LOAD-BEARING because the
                  validate_resolved_transition subflow's GlideRecord
                  query filters on status='Closed' (case-sensitive
                  equality through the != negation); a typo in this
                  status would either (a) cause the choice-list
                  dictionary rejection at insert time, OR (b) silently
                  slip through as an unregistered string that fails
                  the resolve-blocker check inconsistently. Verifiable
                  with: grep -E '<status>Closed</status>' returns
                  exactly 1 match in this file.)

